{
  "document_id": "ps-48",
  "title": "Psalms 48",
  "type": "study-bible",
  "translation": "NJPS",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "A song. A psalm of the Korahites."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "The Lord is great and much acclaimed in the city of our God, His holy mountain—"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "fair-crested, joy of all the earth, Mount Zion, summit of Zaphon, city of the great king."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-3-commentary-1",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "A term for the divine abode.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "ps",
        "chapter": 48,
        "verse": 3
      },
      "verse_start": 3,
      "verse_end": 3
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "Through its citadels, God has made Himself known as a haven."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "See, the kings joined forces; they advanced together."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "At the mere sight of it they were stunned, they were terrified, they panicked;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "they were seized there with a trembling, like a woman in the throes of labor,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "as the Tarshish fleet was wrecked in an easterly gale."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-8-commentary-2",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "See 1 Kings 22.49.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "ps",
        "chapter": 48,
        "verse": 8
      },
      "verse_start": 8,
      "verse_end": 8
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "The likes of what we heard we have now witnessed in the city of the Lord of hosts, in the city of our God— may God preserve it forever! Selah."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "In Your temple, God, we meditate upon Your faithful care."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "The praise of You, God, like Your name, reaches to the ends of the earth; Your right hand is filled with beneficence."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "Let Mount Zion rejoice! Let the towns of Judah exult, because of Your judgments."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-12-commentary-3",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "Or “women.”",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "ps",
        "chapter": 48,
        "verse": 12
      },
      "verse_start": 12,
      "verse_end": 12
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "Walk around Zion, circle it; count its towers,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "take note of its ramparts; go through its citadels, that you may recount it to a future age."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-14-commentary-4",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "Meaning of Heb. uncertain.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "ps",
        "chapter": 48,
        "verse": 14
      },
      "verse_start": 14,
      "verse_end": 14
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "For God—He is our God forever; He will lead us evermore."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-48-15-commentary-5",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "Meaning of Heb. uncertain.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "ps",
        "chapter": 48,
        "verse": 15
      },
      "verse_start": 15,
      "verse_end": 15
    }
  ]
}